\begin_layout Subsection
Estimation
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset CommandInset label
LatexCommand label
name "subsec:estimation"

\end_inset

[Placeholder describing the estimation strategy.
 Intent-to-treat (ITT) effects are estimated using OLS with CR2 cluster-robust
 standard errors (clubSandwich).
 Local Average Treatment Effects (LATE) are estimated via two-stage least
 squares, instrumenting actual use of the measurement and monitoring system
 with random assignment.
 The orthogonalized factorial specification follows Muralidharan et al.,
 using demeaned treatment indicators to isolate individual treatment effects
 that are invariant to the other treatment arm.
 Anderson indices are constructed as summary measures across outcome families.
 Statistical inference in the main text uses Fisher randomization inference
 (RI) p-values, computed from 5,000 permutations that respect the experimental
 design: the measurement and monitoring system treatment is permuted at the
 MCC level (maintaining the number of treated MCCs), and the video treatment
 is permuted within each MCC (maintaining counts).
 For multiple testing, we report an omnibus count test following the EGAP
 approach: under the sharp null of no treatment effect, we compute the
 probability of observing as many individually significant outcomes as in
 the actual data.
 CR2 cluster-robust p-values, Anderson-Sharp q-values, and Westfall-Young
 stepdown-adjusted p-values are reported in the appendix.]
\end_layout

