\begin_layout Subsection
Design
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset CommandInset label
LatexCommand label
name "subsec:exp2-design"

\end_inset

[Placeholder describing Experiment 2 design.
 Among MCCs that received the quality measurement and digital monitoring
 system in Experiment 1, we randomly assign quality bonuses that create
 explicit price incentives for milk quality.
 This exogenously activates the price channel (sets alpha > 0 in the model),
 leveraging the digital quality records already in place to implement quality-based
 payments.]
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Intervention
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset CommandInset label
LatexCommand label
name "subsec:exp2-intervention"

\end_inset

[Placeholder describing the quality bonus intervention.
 Traders delivering milk above a fat content threshold receive a price bonus,
 calculated from the quality readings recorded by the digital monitoring
 system.
 The bonus creates a direct link between measured quality and price, which
 was absent under the enforcement-only equilibrium observed in Experiment
 1.
 The digital bookkeeping system is essential to this intervention: it provides
 the verifiable quality records on which bonus payments are based.]
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Two Stages
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset CommandInset label
LatexCommand label
name "subsec:two-stages"

\end_inset

[Placeholder describing the two-stage design of Experiment 2.
 Stage 1 uses a lower fat threshold (3.3%) that most farmers can achieve.
 Stage 2 raises the threshold (3.9%) to test whether farmers respond to
 more demanding quality standards.
 This allows us to examine the intensive margin of quality improvement.]
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Data
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset CommandInset label
LatexCommand label
name "subsec:exp2-data"

\end_inset

[Placeholder describing the data sources for Experiment 2.
 Daily milk submission records from the digital monitoring system (fat content,
 SNF, quantity), which provides continuous quality tracking at each delivery.
 Endline survey data from traders and farmers.
 Administrative records on bonus payments, calculated from the digitalized
 quality records.]
\end_layout

